Invoking: `validate` with `{'patch': '--- a/Modules/_lsprof.c
+++ b/Modules/_lsprof.c
@@ -769,6 +769,13 @@
 }
+
+    // Free the freelist as well to avoid use-after-free
+    while (pObj->freelistProfilerContext) {
+        ProfilerContext *c = pObj->freelistProfilerContext;
+        pObj->freelistProfilerContext = c->previous;
+        PyMem_Free(c);
+    }
+    pObj->freelistProfilerContext = NULL;
'}`
responded: The freelist (`freelistProfilerContext`) is not cleared in `flush_unmatched`, so after disabling the profiler, the freelist may still contain pointers to contexts that have been freed, leading to use-after-free when reusing these contexts.

**The correct fix is to free the freelist in `flush_unmatched` as well.**  
This matches the logic in `clearEntries`, which frees both `currentProfilerContext` and the freelist.

Here is the correct patch:

args.patch:
diff --git a/Modules/_lsprof.c b/Modules/_lsprof.c
index 5cf9eba243b..c2e640ea10a 100644
--- a/Modules/_lsprof.c
+++ b/Modules/_lsprof.c
@@ -766,6 +766,14 @@ flush_unmatched(ProfilerObject *pObj)
             PyMem_Free(pContext);
     }

+    // Free the freelist as well to avoid use-after-free
+    while (pObj->freelistProfilerContext) {
+        ProfilerContext *c = pObj->freelistProfilerContext;
+        pObj->freelistProfilerContext = c->previous;
+        PyMem_Free(c);
+    }
+    pObj->freelistProfilerContext = NULL;
+
 }

