Invoking: `validate` with `{'patch': '--- a/Modules/_lsprof.c\n+++ b/Modules/_lsprof.c\n@@ -756,15 +756,30 @@\n static void\n flush_unmatched(ProfilerObject *pObj)\n {\n-    while (pObj->currentProfilerContext) {\n-        ProfilerContext *pContext = pObj->currentProfilerContext;\n-        ProfilerEntry *profEntry= pContext->ctxEntry;\n-        if (profEntry)\n-            Stop(pObj, pContext, profEntry);\n-        else\n-            pObj->currentProfilerContext = pContext->previous;\n-        if (pContext)\n-            PyMem_Free(pContext);\n-    }\n-\n-}\n+    while (pObj->currentProfilerContext) {\n+        ProfilerContext *pContext = pObj->currentProfilerContext;\n+        ProfilerEntry *profEntry = pContext->ctxEntry;\n+        if (profEntry) {\n+            // Stop updates currentProfilerContext!\n+            Stop(pObj, pContext, profEntry);\n+            // Do NOT free here; ptr was attached to freelist in ptrace_leave_call, so will be handled below.\n+        } else {\n+            pObj->currentProfilerContext = pContext->previous;\n+            PyMem_Free(pContext);\n+        }\n+    }\n+    // Free any remaining contexts in the freelist\n+    while (pObj->freelistProfilerContext) {\n+        ProfilerContext *c = pObj->freelistProfilerContext;\n+        pObj->freelistProfilerContext = c->previous;\n+        PyMem_Free(c);\n+    }\n+    pObj->freelistProfilerContext = NULL;\n+}\n'}`
responded: The bug is almost certainly that `pObj->currentProfilerContext` isn't actually being updated in the `Stop` branch of the logic in `flush_unmatched`, because `Stop` will set it. However, after calling `Stop(pObj, pContext, profEntry)` we *don't* update `pContext` or the loop condition before freeing, so `pContext` now points to a structure that's already removed from the list (and `currentProfilerContext` is already updated). This can allow the same `ProfilerContext*` to be freed multiple times or for the freelist to pick up a pointer to garbage.

The correct pattern is:
- After `Stop(...)`, do NOT free `pContext`, because `Stop` will update `currentProfilerContext`; we should now use the newly updated `pObj->currentProfilerContext` for the next iteration.
- Only free `pContext` if we update `currentProfilerContext` ourselves (the `else` branch).
- At the end of draining all contexts, free the freelist and set its pointer to NULL.

Let's make a patch that reflects the correct logic:

```diff
--- a/Modules/_lsprof.c
+++ b/Modules/_lsprof.c
@@ -756,15 +756,30 @@
 static void
 flush_unmatched(ProfilerObject *pObj)
 {
-    while (pObj->currentProfilerContext) {
-        ProfilerContext *pContext = pObj->currentProfilerContext;
-        ProfilerEntry *profEntry= pContext->ctxEntry;
-        if (profEntry)
-            Stop(pObj, pContext, profEntry);
-        else
-            pObj->currentProfilerContext = pContext->previous;
-        if (pContext)
-            PyMem_Free(pContext);
-    }
-
-}
+    while (pObj->currentProfilerContext) {
+        ProfilerContext *pContext = pObj->currentProfilerContext;
+        ProfilerEntry *profEntry = pContext->ctxEntry;
+        if (profEntry) {
+            // Stop updates currentProfilerContext!
+            Stop(pObj, pContext, profEntry);
+            // Do NOT free here; ptr was attached to freelist in ptrace_leave_call, so will be handled below.
+        } else {
+            pObj->currentProfilerContext = pContext->previous;
+            PyMem_Free(pContext);
+        }
+    }
+    // Free any remaining contexts in the freelist
+    while (pObj->freelistProfilerContext) {
+        ProfilerContext *c = pObj->freelistProfilerContext;
+        pObj->freelistProfilerContext = c->previous;
+        PyMem_Free(c);
+    }
+    pObj->freelistProfilerContext = NULL;
+}
```
